# üÜï 2025 Generative AI Python Libraries / Projects

This document highlights notable **2025 generative AI Python libraries / frameworks**, their purpose, and installation instructions.

| Library / Project                          | What it is / Why it matters                                                                                                             | Notes / Release or evidence | Install |
| ------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------- |
| **GenAI Processors (by Google DeepMind)**  | A lightweight Python library for orchestration of generative-AI workflows (real-time, multimodal).                                      | Released in 2025 under Apache-2.0. ([MarkTechPost][1])                                                                                  | `pip install genai-processors` |
| **GAICo**                                  | A Python framework for evaluating generative AI outputs (text, images, etc.), cross-modal comparison, metrics, reporting.               | Released on PyPI in June 2025. ([arXiv][2])                                                                                             | `pip install gaico` |
| **Samila**                                 | A generative art Python library (algorithmic / mathematical) for creating visual compositions.                                          | Paper released April 2025. ([arXiv][3])                                                                                                 | `pip install samila` |
| **‚ÄúNew Transformers model releases 2025‚Äù** | The Transformers community is actively pushing new model releases as of April 2025. ([Hugging Face][4])                                 | The ‚ÄúNew Transformers Model Releases ‚Äì 22nd April 2025‚Äù discussion indicates continued updates. ([Hugging Face][4])                     | `pip install transformers --upgrade` |
| **Diffusers / video gen roadmap**          | The Diffusers project is explicitly planning to expand video generation, more adapters, distillation, etc. in 2025. ([Hugging Face][5]) | The blog mentions ‚ÄúLooking ahead ‚Ä¶ anticipate significant advancements in video generation models throughout 2025.‚Äù ([Hugging Face][5]) | `pip install diffusers --upgrade` |

[1]: https://www.marktechpost.com/2025/07/13/google-deepmind-releases-genai-processors-a-lightweight-python-library-that-enables-efficient-and-parallel-content-processing/?utm_source=chatgpt.com "Google DeepMind Releases GenAI Processors - MarkTechPost"
[2]: https://arxiv.org/abs/2508.16753?utm_source=chatgpt.com "GAICo: A Deployed and Extensible Framework for Evaluating Diverse and Multimodal Generative AI Outputs"
[3]: https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.04298?utm_source=chatgpt.com "Samila: A Generative Art Generator"
[4]: https://huggingface.co/spaces/transformers-community/support/discussions?utm_source=chatgpt.com "transformers-community/support ¬∑ Discussions"
[5]: https://huggingface.co/blog/video_gen?utm_source=chatgpt.com "State of open video generation models in Diffusers"

